Job Profile:
Reporting to the Director of I.T., the successful applicant will be responsible and accountable to design, develop and deploy various mobile application architectures across multiple platforms whilst recommending and incorporating the newest mobile technologies for the advancement of our overarching mobile strategy.
Job Responsibilities / Duties:
1. Leading the architecture, design and implementation of new mobile applications for both iOS and Android by:

Identifying opportunities to develop new mobile applications that will benefit the organization(s) and members;
Conducting market research and bringing forward a solid project proposal and business case relating to the opportunities you have identified;
Performing UI/UX design and creating draft wireframes and prototypes that will establish the foundation for all mobile application development projects;
Taking a concept and theme from a “sketch” or framework in illustrator all the way to a live mobile application;
Writing clean, readable and testable code that is highly reliable;
Partnering closely with key stakeholders to continually shape both the technical, functional, and aesthetic direction of the application being developed;
Ensuring quality and performance of the mobile applications to required specifications;
Performing testing, identifying potential problems, and making sound recommendations on how to resolve any issues as they arise;
Overseeing the pre-launch of a beta version of the mobile application for use and testing by key stakeholders prior to final release;
Ensuring all application bugs are resolved prior to final release;
Publishing the final mobile applications to the app stores;
Providing timely and accurate updates to the Director of I.T.

2. To maintain, monitor and troubleshoot all mobile applications throughout their lifecycle by:

Continually reviewing existing mobile applications to simplify and align them more closely with user needs;
Identifying and planning for new features or feature improvements;
Designing, coding and implementing application updates over time;
Ensuring all mobile application appropriately integrate with other platforms and technologies as required without detrimentally impacting the mobile applications in production;
Ensure the upkeep of the mobile applications’ code quality and ensure continual code evaluation.

3. Other job duties and special projects as may be assigned by the Business Manager, Director of I.T., and/or the Human Resources Department.
Job Requirements:

Post-secondary education in Computer Engineering, Computer Programing, or similar;
Certification in Mobile Application Development, User Interface and/or User Experience Design;
Minimum 3-5 years of programming experience, specifically in the field of mobile application development;
A demonstrated portfolio of work in on mobile application development projects;
Experience working with APIs;
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
Proven ability to meet deadlines;
Able to develop ideas and processes and clearly express them;
Experience in graphic design & UI/UX design work would be considered an asset;
Experience with both Microsoft and Apple (mac) systems;
Excellent written, oral and telephone communication skills;
Able to communicate in user-friendly language;
Exceptional multi-tasking abilities and prioritization skills;
A team player who is able to work effectively under pressure;
A high level of confidentiality and professionalism at all times;
Able to thrive in a fast-paced environment;
Willing and able to travel between offices as needed;
Must have valid license and regular access to a vehicle;
Experience with SQL, MySQL database systems;
Strong background in code development, specifically in Java, HTML, PHP, & JavaScript;
Solid knowledge and experience in programming languages, terminology and applications.

If you are qualified and interested in this position, please submit your resume, to the attention of the Director of Human Resources, outlining your qualifications and suitability to this position.
